The '''Shattered Relics League glitch''' was a major [[glitch]] that occurred on [[19 January]] [[2022]]. With the release of [[Shattered Relics League]], there were problems with player profiles. Some players lost their [[Ironman Mode]] status upon logging back into the main game after logging into a Shattered Relics League world, and some players had their main game items and stats transferred over to their Shattered Relics League profile.

Jagex turned the game offline around an hour after the update to perform a rollback.{{CiteTwitter|author=Old School RuneScape|url=https://twitter.com/OldSchoolRS/status/1483786055174303751|date=19 January 2022|archiveurl=https://archive.ph/HquQZ|archivedate=8 April 2022|quote=Due to issues with League save profiles, we are going to be shutting the game down very shortly. Unfortunately, we are required to perform a rollback to just before the launch of Leagues III. Apologies for the inconvenience and we will update you with more information soon.}} The rollback only affected main game profiles and not Shattered Relics.{{CiteTwitter|author=Old School RuneScape|url=https://twitter.com/OldSchoolRS/status/1483790564499808257|date=19 January 2022|archiveurl=https://archive.ph/Wkt43|archivedate=8 April 2022|quote=We've identified that the rollback will only be required for main game progress, setting players back to just before the update. The Hiscores for Leagues will be reset, but all progress made on a Leagues world will be available when the game is back online.}}

Several hours after the update, Jagex acknowledged the rollback had caused some [[Group Ironman Mode]] shared storage items to have been deleted.{{CiteTwitter|author=Old School RuneScape|url=https://twitter.com/OldSchoolRS/status/1483864160102404104|date=19 January 2022|archiveurl=https://archive.ph/AkWTl|archivedate=8 April 2022|quote=Following the rollback that was performed earlier today, some items from Group Storage have been lost. We are currently investigating potential solutions and identifying those who may have been affected.}}

